## ğŸŒ¸ 1. **Association (uses-a relationship)**

### ğŸ”¹ Concept:

Association ka matlab hota hai **â€œek class dusri class ka object use karti haiâ€**, lekin dono **independent** hote hain.
Yani agar ek class delete ho jaaye, dusri class fir bhi exist karti hai.

**Example:**
Ek `Teacher` ek `Department` me kaam karta hai â€” dono alag entities hain.

### ğŸ”¹ UML Diagram (Text Style)

```
Teacher  â€”â€”â€”  Department
 (uses-a)
```

### ğŸ”¹ Code:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class Department {
public:
    string deptName;
    Department(string name) {
        deptName = name;
    }
};

class Teacher {
public:
    string teacherName;
    Teacher(string name) {
        teacherName = name;
    }

    void showDepartment(Department &d) {
        cout << teacherName << " works in " << d.deptName << " department." << endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    Department d("Computer Science");
    Teacher t("Geetika");
    t.showDepartment(d);
    return 0;
}
```

### ğŸ”¹ Output:

```
Geetika works in Computer Science department.
```

### ğŸ”¹ Explanation:

Yahan `Teacher` class **use kar rahi hai** `Department` class ka object â€” thatâ€™s **Association**.
Dono alag-alag exist kar sakte hain.

